value.title: Biden will move US closer to 2015 nuclear deal with Iran, experts say
value.excerpt: Foreign policy experts and those close to President-elect Joe Biden believe he will move the U.S. closer to the 2015 nuclear deal with Iran, but that it will be no easy task.

value.title: Xavier Becerra, possible Biden AG pick, once said illegal immigration should be decriminalized
value.excerpt: California Attorney General Xavier Becerra, who Fox News is told is being considered to serve as attorney general in the upcoming Biden administration, once said that illegal immigration should be decriminalized -- one of a number of radical stances he has taken on the subject.

value.title: Candace Owens: Newsom will follow 'Marxist' BLM, appoint Black woman to replace Kamala Harris in Senate
value.excerpt: California Gov. Gavin Newsom will bend the knee to Black Lives Matter, author Candace Owens argued on Wednesday, reacting to the organization calling on Newsom to appoint a Black woman to fill the senate seat vacated by Kamala Harris.

value.title: AOC-linked group advises Biden to pass economic agenda 'with or without formal legislation'
value.excerpt: A progressive group with ties to Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y., is privately advising President-elect Joe Biden to move forward with his economic agenda whether or not Democrats win control of the Senate in a pair of Georgia runoffs early next year.

value.title: 'Just ridiculous': CNN speaks to Georgia voter the Trump campaign falsely accused of casting ballot in the name of a dead woman
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's campaign and Fox News host Tucker Carlson alleged last week that a vote cast by a Georgia woman named Deborah Jean Christiansen was fraudulent.

value.title: Mike Lee calls on Sen. Feinstein to apologize for inaccurate claim of Trump inciting violence
value.excerpt: Sen. Dianne Feinstein, D-Calif., is wrong about President Trump's tweets inciting violence, Sen. Mike Lee, R-Utah, said Wednesday.

value.title: Patsy Takemoto Mink blazed the trail for Kamala Harris – not famous white woman Susan B. Anthony
value.excerpt: Her victory comes one century after the 19th Amendment, which gave American women the right to vote. Many commentators quickly linked Harris’ achievement to activist Susan B. Anthony. Anthony did advocate for the 19th Amendment.

value.title: Trump faces Wednesday deadline for Wisconsin vote recount
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump faces a Wednesday deadline to file for a recount in Wisconsin after Democrat Joe Biden defeated him in the state by more than 20,600 votes based on final canvassed totals. The totals submitted by all 72 counties to the state elections commission showed Trump with a roughly six-tenths of a point margin — close enough for Trump to file for a recount.

value.title: 'This is extremely powerful data': Trump's 2020 campaign app manufacturer in financial trouble
value.excerpt: The "Official Trump 2020 App" allowed President Trump's reelection campaign to monitor the movements of his supporters.

value.title: Election 2020 Live Updates: Biden staffs up as Trump fires top election security official
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden began staffing up this week, announcing the hiring of nine senior White House officials, including top members of his campaign and longtime aides, as he pushes ahead with the transition process.

value.title: Trump Hasn't Conceded Georgia. Neither Did Stacey Abrams. What Changed?
value.excerpt: The president's refusal to acknowledge defeat isn't the first time Georgia voters have heard that, but state officials say claims about impropriety — past and present — are false.

value.title: Trump lashes out in new bid to tarnish an election he lost
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump flexed the power of his office Tuesday to tarnish America's free and fair election, sacking the official who declared the vote the most secure in US history, even as more of his false claims of massive fraud were exposed as baseless in court.

value.title: Trump fires top U.S. election cybersecurity official who defended vote
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Tuesday fired top cybersecurity official Chris Krebs in a message on Twitter, accusing him without evidence of making a "highly inaccurate" statement affirming the Nov. 3 election was secure and rejecting claims of fraud.

value.title: US drops 'strong' case against ex-Mexico defense chief Salvador Cienfuegos, a 'huge gift' from Donald Trump, former DEA official says
value.excerpt: Salvador Cienfuegos, arrested in Los Angeles last month on drug trafficking and money laundering charges, faced 10 years in U.S. prison if convicted.

value.title: Advice for Biden? We Want to Hear Yours
value.excerpt: We ask readers how the incoming president should confront the serious challenges that will face him. What do you see as the greatest challenge facing Joe Biden’s presidency? What advice would you give him to overcome it and avoid the pitfalls?

value.title: Twitter fact-checks Donald Trump tweet about the firing of Chris Krebs (on Twitter)
value.excerpt: Twitter appended a label to fact-check President Donald Trump’s tweet about his firing of the nation’s top election security official Chris Krebs.

value.title: The Point: Lindsey Graham just crossed another line in defending Trump
value.excerpt: Fresh off a surprisingly pedestrian election win on November 3, Lindsey Graham has decided to take on a new role: The most aggressive enforcer of the idea that President Donald Trump maybe -- just maybe! -- didn't lose the 2020 election.

value.title: Trump and Army secretary say Wreaths Across America event will happen, reversing Arlington National Cemetery decision
value.excerpt: Wreaths Across America's annual wreath-laying ceremony at Arlington National Cemetery is set to go forward as planned after all.

value.title: Trump administration moves to limit work permits for immigrants with deportation orders
value.excerpt: The Trump administration on Tuesday announced that it was moving to limit work permits for immigrants who have deportation orders, but have been temporarily released -- a move that officials say will encourage them to remove themselves from the country.

value.title: Election 2020 live updates: GOP colleagues congratulate Harris; Biden speaks to Netanyahu
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden on Tuesday spoke to Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi.
